detaileddescription.para:
Example devicetree fragment: spi@... {
        cs-gpios = <&gpio0 1 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>;
        spidev: spi-device@0 { ... };
};
 Assume that gpio0 follows the standard convention for specifying GPIOs, i.e. it has the following in its binding: gpio-cells:
- pin
- flags
 Example usage: struct spi_cs_control *ctrl =
        SPI_CS_CONTROL_PTR_DT(DT_NODELABEL(spidev), 2);
 This example is equivalent to: struct spi_cs_control *ctrl =
        &(struct spi_cs_control) {
                .gpio_dev = DEVICE_DT_GET(DT_NODELABEL(gpio0)),
                .delay = 2,
                .gpio_pin = 1,
                .gpio_dt_flags = GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW
        };
 This macro is not available in C++.
